tldr: The user requested to implement a database for a sleep questionnaire
  application, including an admin dashboard with login and CSV export. The
  project involved setting up a PostgreSQL database with Prisma, creating API
  routes for data storage and retrieval, and building a simple admin interface
  with Next.js middleware for authentication.
overview: The user's intent was to add database functionality and an admin
  dashboard to a sleep questionnaire application based on a provided Statement
  of Work. The approach involved updating the application's data models to
  include  and  fields, and creating a
  model in Prisma for PostgreSQL. API routes were developed for submitting
  questionnaire data, retrieving all responses, and exporting them as a CSV. For
  authentication, a simple password-based system was implemented, initially with
  custom session management, but later streamlined using Next.js middleware to
  protect the admin dashboard and API routes. The database setup was guided, and
  the functionality was thoroughly tested, including questionnaire submission,
  admin login, and CSV export, confirming all requirements were met.
